"a.难取悦的，挑剔的 【英】 adj.难取悦的，挑剔 的(not easy to please ; very critical or discriminating; dainty); 【考】 devoted : zealous / careful : fastidious(过分热衷是狂热/过 分仔细是挑剔)反义词：indiscrimin ate(不加区分的); coarse(粗俗的); easygoing(易于交往 的); uncritical(不严厉的) 【记】 fast(绝食)+tidious( =tedious,乏味的)→ 因乏味而绝食→挑剔的 【同】 同根词：fasting(禁 食) 【例】 She helped the fastidious customer try on all kinds of clothes for an hour. adj. (在味道和礼节方面)挑剔的(过分注意细节, 难于取悦的) = dainty = exacting 【记】fast绝食, tidious = tedious(adj 单调乏味的)－因单调乏味而绝食－挑剔的 【类】devoted: zealous = careful: fastidious 过分热衷是狂热 = 过分仔细是挑剔fastidious: outshine = recalcitrant: resist过分讲究的比别人漂亮 = 反抗的抵抗dapper: fastidious 衣冠楚楚的: 过分讲究的 【反】indiscriminate(adj 不加选择的; 不加区分的); coarse(adj 粗糙的; 粗俗的); uncritical(adj 不严厉的)easygoing(adj 逍遥自在的; 放荡的; 不严肃的); cursory(adj 匆匆忙忙的; 草率的) 【记】fast 绝食 + tidious (tedious,乏味的)→绝食，因为吃什么都觉得乏味→太挑剔 fastidious (adj.)  mid-15c., ""full of pride,"" from Latin fastidiosus ""disdainful, squeamish, exacting,"" from fastidium ""loathing, squeamishness,"" most likely from *fastu-taidiom, a compound of fastus ""contempt, arrogance"" and taedium ""aversion, disgust."" Early use in English was both in passive and active senses. Meaning ""squeamish, over-nice"" emerged in English 1610s. Related: Fastidiously; fastidiousness."
